A drunk driver forced terrified motorists out of his way when he drove into on-coming traffic for three miles around a city centre the wrong way.

John Rixon, 31, had smoked cannabis and was nearly twice over the limit when he set off in his silver Audi to drive 25 miles home at midnight after visiting a friend.

But he found himself on the gyratory system in Bristol city centre  - heading the wrong way.

