CCTV operators alerted police after Rixon ignored warnings from other motorists and drove on until he found himself in a dead end blocked by bollards.

He then reversed and went back onto the city centre system, still on the wrong side of the road, and heading straight towards oncoming drivers.

His 15 minutes of mayhem ended when he crashed into a taxi driver and another motorist driving the wrong way around a roundabout.

Rixon abandoned his car and tried to run away but he was rugby-tackled to the ground by a policeman.

